{
  "stem": "23090.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I do remember that the-- the frequency was very-- was very much that we did at least-- at least once or twice a week perform the Judaism as we do in temple here.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Plus, there was always some [NON-ENGLISH] that the men were performing for people that passed on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had the traditional cooking of the cholent, which I would-- since I was the only boy, I was delegated on a Friday to stand in line and carry the big pot of cholent to the baker.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I got my number and-- and the next day we would stand in line.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The line seemed like it was forever when we picked up the cholent.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the smell and the wonderful aura was like heaven.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was a very big thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The whole families were-- got together for that occasion, which was Saturday around 11, 12 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was a wonderful-- a wonderful thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a-- it's like a family getting together, you know, on an annual basis for a great picnic, where you read, where everyone gets together and just has a wonderful, close time.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that's what Shabbos represented to us-- to me as a young boy, that it was an opportunity to see everyone.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there was happiness and cheerfulness and it was a wonderful feeling.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It made you feel close, that you had a family and that you were part of a very close-knitted family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So if that's interpreting being religious, then I-- we were religious.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But taking it to another extreme, perhaps we were not.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Definitely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Seders were-- seders were rituals.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
